; Section 3.1 - Variables, Syntactic Keywords, and Regions
;
; This section is largely definitional.  The two explicitly stated errors are:
;   - referencing an unbound variable
;   - using a syntactic keyword where a value expression is expected

; ==========================================================================
; Unbound variable reference
; ==========================================================================

>>> undefined-variable

%%% %any-error%

>>> (+ undefined-variable 1)

%%% %any-error%

>>> (car undefined-variable)

%%% %any-error%

